pairwise.reason: Left has better expression for dad and cute motion for baby. Right is pretty good, too -- especially the seemingly knowing expression for baby. But dad's vacant expression is pretty lame.

They're both pretty good! The picture on the left is super cute -- baby's eyes are wide, she's staring at us, she's well framed. On the right she's pretty cute, too, but smaller and slouchy. So left is better but both are share-worthy.

These photos are both okay -- not great, but okay. The swing photo isn't special -- not well framed, baby isn't doing anything particularly interesting. The eating the plastic lemon photo is better -- it's funny -- but it's still pretty zoomed out and the lighting contrast is worse.

The photo on the right is slightly better, but they're both pretty good. Baby is engaged in both, and the photo quality is definitely better on the left. But baby is super engaged -- with a funny expression -- on the right, and it seems to capture a more intimate moment.
Photo B -- the mischief and joy are the best!
Baby looks ornery in the expression on the left. On the right is okay -- neutral expression, tight shot.
The left photo is more about daddy, the right photo is more about baby. And the interaction of daddy looking at baby is nice.
Can't really tell what's going on in the photo on the right.

The photo on the right because it looks like dad and daughter are enjoying something together. The smile is awesome on the left but it's kinda weird that dad is looking one way and daughter in another.
Both good. Baby looks so cool on the left. Baby looks so unhappy on the right -- comically so when daddy is being so loving.
Can't see the baby's face enough in Photo A.
Mom's expressions are not the best despite baby looking cute.
Photo on the left is slightly better. It's a tighter shot of baby, baby is clearly engaged in play. Photo B looks a little posed and too far away.
Photo A has baby much more interactive, and a tighter shot. Photo B -- who knows where the baby is looking and only a tiny part of the photo.
The moment of wonder in Photo B makes it the winner!
